MLflow Quiz: Questions and Answers

1. What is the primary purpose of MLflow?
A. Container orchestration
B. Machine learning lifecycle management  <-- Answer: B
C. Database administration
D. Web application hosting

2. Which company originally developed MLflow?
A. Google
B. Microsoft
C. Databricks  <-- Answer: C
D. IBM

3. Which programming language is most commonly associated with MLflow?
A. Java
B. Python  <-- Answer: B
C. C++
D. Go

4. Which MLflow component is used for experiment tracking?
A. MLflow Models
B. MLflow Projects
C. MLflow Tracking  <-- Answer: C
D. MLflow Registry

5. What can MLflow Tracking record?
A. Parameters, metrics, and artifacts  <-- Answer: A
B. Only metrics
C. Only datasets
D. Only model files

6. What is an Experiment in MLflow?
A. A database table
B. A collection of related runs  <-- Answer: B
C. A trained model
D. A deployment target

7. What is a Run in MLflow?
A. A deployment instance
B. A single execution of a machine learning workflow  <-- Answer: B
C. A Docker container
D. A database connection

8. Which function starts a new MLflow run?
A. mlflow.run()
B. mlflow.start_run()  <-- Answer: B
C. mlflow.begin_run()
D. mlflow.track_run()

9. Which method logs a parameter?
A. mlflow.log_metric()
B. mlflow.log_artifact()
C. mlflow.log_param()  <-- Answer: C
D. mlflow.save_param()

10. Which method logs a metric?
A. mlflow.log_metric()  <-- Answer: A
B. mlflow.metric_log()
C. mlflow.save_metric()
D. mlflow.record_metric()

11. What is an Artifact in MLflow?
A. A hyperparameter
B. An output file produced during a run  <-- Answer: B
C. A deployment endpoint
D. A database record

12. Which method logs artifacts?
A. mlflow.log_artifact()  <-- Answer: A
B. mlflow.save_artifact()
C. mlflow.track_artifact()
D. mlflow.artifact_log()

13. What is the purpose of MLflow Projects?
A. Model deployment only
B. Packaging ML code for reproducibility  <-- Answer: B
C. Logging metrics only
D. Database integration

14. Which file commonly defines an MLflow Project?
A. requirements.txt
B. MLproject  <-- Answer: B
C. project.yml
D. mlflow.yaml

15. What is the purpose of MLflow Models?
A. Version control source code
B. Standardize model packaging and deployment  <-- Answer: B
C. Store datasets
D. Manage containers

16. What is the Model Registry used for?
A. Tracking experiments
B. Managing model versions and lifecycle stages  <-- Answer: B
C. Logging datasets
D. Running notebooks

17. Which stage is commonly associated with a production-ready model?
A. Draft
B. Testing
C. Production  <-- Answer: C
D. Archived

18. Which stage is used for evaluating models before production?
A. Development
B. Staging  <-- Answer: B
C. Deployment
D. Validation

19. Which command starts the MLflow Tracking UI?
A. mlflow start-ui
B. mlflow ui  <-- Answer: B
C. mlflow dashboard
D. mlflow track-ui

20. By default, on which port does the MLflow UI run?
A. 5000  <-- Answer: A
B. 8080
C. 3306
D. 9000

21. Which MLflow component manages model lifecycle?
A. Tracking
B. Registry  <-- Answer: B
C. Projects
D. Artifacts

22. What is a Tracking Server?
A. Server that stores experiment metadata  <-- Answer: A
B. Server that hosts notebooks
C. Server for model inference only
D. Kubernetes node

23. Which method logs an entire machine learning model?
A. mlflow.log_model()
B. mlflow.save_model()
C. Framework-specific log_model methods  <-- Answer: C
D. mlflow.track_model()

24. Which MLflow flavor is used for Scikit-learn models?
A. mlflow.keras
B. mlflow.pytorch
C. mlflow.sklearn  <-- Answer: C
D. mlflow.tensorflowlite

25. Which MLflow flavor supports TensorFlow models?
A. mlflow.tensorflow  <-- Answer: A
B. mlflow.tflite
C. mlflow.deepai
D. mlflow.neural

26. Which MLflow flavor supports PyTorch models?
A. mlflow.torchvision
B. mlflow.pytorch  <-- Answer: B
C. mlflow.deep-learning
D. mlflow.neuralnet

27. What is a Model Flavor?
A. Model deployment region
B. Framework-specific representation of a model  <-- Answer: B
C. Dataset format
D. Hyperparameter configuration

28. What is the purpose of model signatures?
A. Store source code
B. Define model inputs and outputs  <-- Answer: B
C. Encrypt models
D. Create experiments

29. Which MLflow component improves reproducibility?
A. Projects  <-- Answer: A
B. Registry
C. UI
D. Stages

30. Which backend database can MLflow use?
A. MySQL
B. PostgreSQL
C. SQLite
D. All of the above  <-- Answer: D

31. What is a Tracking URI?
A. Model deployment URL
B. Location of the MLflow Tracking Server  <-- Answer: B
C. Database password
D. Dataset path

32. Which method sets the tracking URI?
A. mlflow.set_uri()
B. mlflow.set_tracking_uri()  <-- Answer: B
C. mlflow.configure_uri()
D. mlflow.set_server_uri()

33. What is nested run functionality used for?
A. Multi-model deployment
B. Organizing related runs hierarchically  <-- Answer: B
C. Parallel training
D. Security management

34. Which method is used to set an experiment?
A. mlflow.create_experiment()
B. mlflow.set_experiment()  <-- Answer: B
C. mlflow.select_experiment()
D. mlflow.use_experiment()

35. What does MLflow autologging provide?
A. Automatic deployment
B. Automatic logging of parameters, metrics, and models  <-- Answer: B
C. Automatic scaling
D. Automatic dataset generation

36. Which method enables autologging?
A. mlflow.enable_log()
B. mlflow.autolog()  <-- Answer: B
C. mlflow.auto_track()
D. mlflow.auto_run()

37. What is a registered model?
A. A deployed model endpoint
B. A model tracked in the Model Registry  <-- Answer: B
C. A training dataset
D. An experiment group

38. Which lifecycle stage typically indicates a retired model?
A. Staging
B. Testing
C. Archived  <-- Answer: C
D. Production

39. What is the benefit of model versioning?
A. Improves GPU utilization
B. Tracks and manages model changes over time  <-- Answer: B
C. Increases training speed
D. Reduces dataset size

40. What can MLflow deploy models to?
A. REST endpoints
B. Cloud platforms
C. Local environments
D. All of the above  <-- Answer: D

41. Which command serves a model locally?
A. mlflow models serve  <-- Answer: A
B. mlflow deploy local
C. mlflow run serve
D. mlflow endpoint create

42. What is the purpose of the MLmodel file?
A. Defines model metadata and flavors  <-- Answer: A
B. Stores training data
C. Stores logs
D. Stores experiment metrics

43. Which MLflow feature supports collaboration between teams?
A. Model Registry  <-- Answer: A
B. Docker Integration
C. Notebook Tracking
D. Hyperparameter Tuning

44. What is a common use case for MLflow Registry?
A. Source code storage
B. Managing model promotion workflows  <-- Answer: B
C. Container management
D. Dataset versioning only

45. Which cloud platforms commonly integrate with MLflow?
A. AWS
B. Azure
C. Google Cloud
D. All of the above  <-- Answer: D

46. What is the primary purpose of artifact storage?
A. Save outputs such as models, plots, and files  <-- Answer: A
B. Store cluster information
C. Manage users
D. Run deployments

47. Which MLflow component is most relevant for experiment comparison?
A. Tracking  <-- Answer: A
B. Registry
C. Projects
D. Deployment

48. What does MLflow help improve in ML projects?
A. Reproducibility
B. Traceability
C. Collaboration
D. All of the above  <-- Answer: D

49. Which type of metric can be logged in MLflow?
A. Accuracy
B. Loss
C. Precision
D. All of the above  <-- Answer: D

50. Which statement best describes MLflow?
A. A database system
B. An end-to-end machine learning lifecycle platform  <-- Answer: B
C. A Kubernetes replacement
D. A web framework for APIs
